a throws out her childhood keepsakes, while Mr. Kim takes Mr. Mehta's advice to use the situation to his advantage. \n |LineColor       = 02A3C8\n |Viewers         =\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 37\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 11\n |Title           = Appanticitis\n |DirectedBy      = Renuka Jeyapalan\n |WrittenBy       = Ins Choi & Kevin White\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|3|19}}\n |ShortSummary    = Mr. Kim invents a new type of clothing. Appa tries to give Umma advice about her annoying habit, but regrets it. Janet takes Gerald to the emergency room when his appendix flares up, not expecting the ER doctor to be her ex, Raj. Jung auditions for the Astounding Trek reality show with Kimchee, but doesn't want him to know that he's also auditioning with Shannon. Umma's new look is not well received.\n |LineColor       = 02A3C8\n |Viewers         =\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 38\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 12\n |Title           = Hit 'n' Fun\n |DirectedBy      = Peter Wellington\n |WrittenBy       = Ins Choi & Kevin White\n |OriginalAirDate =  {{Start date|2019|3|26}}\n |ShortSummary    =  In the church parking lot, Umma backs into Pastor Nina's new car and tries to avoid taking responsibility. After Appa fails to object to Jimmy's sexist jokes, Umma and Appa argue over gender roles and Appa agrees to make the [[Nanaimo bar]]s for the church's bake sale. Janet tries to turn the tables on Gerald after she finds out he and Chelsea have been making fun of her, and ends up getting far closer to Chelsea than she'd wanted. Jung tries to get Shannon's birthday card back when he realizes he wrote \"love, Jung\" on it, but ends up implicating Kimchee.\n |LineColor       = 02A3C8\n |Viewers         =\n}}{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 39\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 13\n |Title           = Lord of the Ring\n |DirectedBy      = Peter Wellington\n |WrittenBy       = Anita Kapila, Matt Kippen, and Kurt Smeaton\n |OriginalAirDate =  {{Start date|2019|4|2}}\n |ShortSummary    = Umma loses her ring; Appa holds off telling her he's found it. Janet and Jung join a yoga class taught by her crush, Nathan. Kimchee and Shannon argue over who gets to keep a barbecue they won. Raj breaks up with his fiancee in hopes of getting back together with Janet, but he may be too late.\n |LineColor       = 02A3C8\n |Viewers         =\n}}\n}}\n\n===Season 4 (2020)===\nOn May 24, 2018, just 2 months after announcing the third season renewal of the show, CBC announced that the show had also been renewed for a fourth season.<ref name=\"Kim's Convenience seasons 3 and 4\" />\n\nA tweet from actor Sugith Varughese on May 21, 2019, stated that filming for season 4 had started.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/SugithVarughese/status/1130825947089969152|title=Thanks. And all 3 seasons are on #Netflix outside Canada and #Gem inside Canada. We just started filming season 4.|first=Sugith|last=Varughese \u00a0\ud83c\udde8\ud83c\udde6|date=May 21, 2019|publisher=}}</ref> Season 4 premiered on January 7, 2020.\n\n{{Episode table |background=#A080FF |overall= |season= |title= |director= |directorR= |writer= |airdate= |episodes= \n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 40\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n |Title           = The Trollop\n |DirectedBy      = Peter Wellington\n |WrittenBy       = Ins Choi & Kevin White\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|1|7}}\n |ShortSummary    = Janet and Raj deal with the aftermath of Raj's broken engagement. Mr. Kim tries to return an expensive dress. Mr. Mehta suspects Raj broke up with his fiancee because of another woman. Shannon gets in trouble when she imitates an accent.\n \n |LineColor       = A080FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 41\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n |Title           = Couch Surfing\n |DirectedBy      = Peter Wellington\n |WrittenBy       = Matt Kippen\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|1|14}}\n |ShortSummary    = When a water pipe bursts in their apartment, Jung goes to stay with Janet and Kimchee stays with the Kims. Janet gets defensive when Jung accuses her of being \"emotionally unavailable\" and her housemates agree. Kimchee becomes the fall guy for Appa's mistakes.\n |LineColor       = A080FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 42\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n |Title           = The Help\n |DirectedBy      = [[Renuka Jeyapalan]]\n |WrittenBy       = Clara Altimas & Matt Kippen\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|1|21}}\n |ShortSummary    = Janet is offended when a rich patron assumes Umma is a food server at her school's art show. Shannon finally breaks up with Alejandro and wants to avoid the rebound. \n |LineColor       = A080FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 43\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n |Title           = Happy Ummaversary\n |DirectedBy      = Renuka Jeyapalan\n |WrittenBy       = Ins Choi & Kevin White\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|1|28}}\n |ShortSummary    = Janet hosts a surprise family dinner for Umma, the family's first dinner together in 15 years. Shannon wants to keep her relationship with Jung a secret. \n |LineColor       = A080FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 44\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n |Title           = Thinkin' 'Bout Inkin'\n |DirectedBy      = Peter Wellington\n |WrittenBy       = Matt Kippen\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|4}}\n |ShortSummary    = Janet wants to get a tattoo. Umma gossips about Pastor Nina. Jung and Shannon exchange five-week-iversary gifts.\n |LineColor       = A080FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 45\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n |Title           = Soccer Dad\n |DirectedBy      = Renuka Jeyapalan\n |WrittenBy       = Ins Choi & Kevin White\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|11}}\n |ShortSummary    = Appa takes it upon himself to coach Jung's beer league soccer team; Shannon plans a birthday party for Stacie, whether she wants one or not; Janet teaches herself how to cook when Umma refuses to make a dish for her housemates.\n |LineColor       = A080FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n 